d in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":29,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Roger Kryton was born in 1261, in Sefton, Lancashire, England as the son of Roger Kryton. He married Alicia de Thweng about 1285, in Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1293, in Lancashire, England, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1261–1293":"1261–1293","1268–1325":"1268–1325","1287–1361":"1287–1361","1289–Male":"1289–Surnud","1244–Male":"1244–Surnud","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1289":"1289","1244":"1244","1287":"1287","1361":"1361","1261":"1261","about 1289":"umbes 1289","1293":"1293","about 1285":"umbes 1285","1290":"1290","Sefton, Lardbrook, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1261–1293":"1261–1293","1268–1325":"1268–1325","1287–1361":"1287–1361","1289–Male":"1289–Kuollut","1244–Male":"1244–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1268":"1268","1289":"1289","1244":"1244","1287":"1287","1361":"1361","1261":"1261","about 1289":"noin 1289","1293":"1293","about 1285":"noin 1285","1290":"1290","Sefton, Lardbrook, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1261–1293":"1261–